Tallinn, the Estonian city of wonder

An aerial shot of Tallinn in winter.

The high temperatures in Kenya have persisted longer than norm. This makes me long for Estonia, a place whose temperatures are as chilly as they can get. I took a trip last year to The Republic of Estonia, a nation in Northern Europe bordering the Baltic Sea and Gulf of Finland and sharing land borders with Latvia and Russia.To get to Estonia, I had to go through Istanbul in a journey that took approximately six hours from Nairobi.
